<h5 id="deploy_operator"><a href="#deploy_operator">Install Operator</a></h5>

<p>To install and deploy the Synopsys Operator navigate to the <b>Operator</b> tab,</p>

<p>If you have an existing version of Operator installed, then youâ€™ll get the Upgrade Operator option.</p>

<img src="/assets/images/operator/nav.png" class="operator-nav" alt=""><br><br>

<ol>
    <li>Type the Polaris Operator version that you want to install and deploy.</li>
    <li>Enter the GCR token (JSON token gathered from prerequisites).</li>
    <li>Click <b>Install</b>.</li>
</ol>

<img src="/assets/images/operator/install.png" class="operator-install" alt="">

<p>Next, you go to the Deploy Polaris or Deploy Black Duck tabs to deploy the Synopsys applications.</p>

<br><br>

<h5 id="upgrade_operator"><a href="#upgrade_operator">Upgrade Operator</a></h5>

<p>Navigate to <b>Operator</b> tab, type the version in the Operator Upgrade field and then click Upgrade.</p>

<img src="/assets/images/operator/nav.png" class="operator-nav" alt=""><br><br>

<p>Enter Operator version to which you would like to upgrade to and click on Upgrade.</p>

<img src="/assets/images/operator/upgrade.png" class="operator-upgrade" alt=""><br><br>

<p>Note: If you are not sure about the version, leave the pre-populated version as it as which is considered to be
    latest release version.</p>

<h7>You have successfully installed Operator ! Proceed for application deployment.</h7>